5:["$","main",null,{"children":["$","article",null,{"className":"pt-32 md:pt-40 pb-24 px-6 md:px-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"rs-eyebrow","style":{"fontSize":"0.7rem","color":"#D22C2E"},"children":["Kitchen economics · ","2026-07-10"," · ",6," min read"]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"rs-display mt-4","style":{"fontSize":"clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3rem)","lineHeight":1.1,"fontWeight":600,"color":"#2A160C"},"children":"How hotels reduce food cost using standardized masalas"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-8 grid gap-5","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"rs-body","style":{"color":"#4A3728","fontSize":"1.02rem","lineHeight":1.85},"children":"Ask any F&B controller where food cost leaks, and they will talk about portioning, wastage and pilferage. Almost nobody mentions the masala shelf — yet in Indian kitchens it quietly drives all three."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"rs-body","style":{"color":"#4A3728","fontSize":"1.02rem","lineHeight":1.85},"children":"When a kitchen grinds or hand-mixes its own masalas, every batch is slightly different. The chef compensates by tasting and adjusting — a little more of this, another ladle of that. Multiply that adjustment across every dish, every shift, and you get unpredictable ingredient draw-down, inconsistent plates, and a menu you cannot cost with confidence."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"rs-body","style":{"color":"#4A3728","fontSize":"1.02rem","lineHeight":1.85},"children":"Standardized masalas attack the problem at the root. A fixed blend with a fixed dosage per recipe means the same plate costs the same amount every single day. Three effects follow:"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"rs-body","style":{"color":"#4A3728","fontSize":"1.02rem","lineHeight":1.85},"children":"1. Costing becomes arithmetic. If your sambhar base uses 320g of blend for 80 plates, your masala cost per plate is a known number — not a range. Menus can be priced on data."}],["$","p","4",{"className":"rs-body","style":{"color":"#4A3728","fontSize":"1.02rem","lineHeight":1.85},"children":"2. Training gets cheaper. A new commis follows a dosage card instead of shadowing a senior for months to 'learn the hand'. Kitchens report faster onboarding and fewer failed batches."}],["$","p","5",{"className":"rs-body","style":{"color":"#4A3728","fontSize":"1.02rem","lineHeight":1.85},"children":"3. Multi-outlet consistency stops being a dream. When every branch draws from the same batch-coded blend, the flagship and the newest outlet serve the same dish. Guests notice — and so do reviews."}],["$","p","6",{"className":"rs-body","style":{"color":"#4A3728","fontSize":"1.02rem","lineHeight":1.85},"children":"The switch pays for itself even at a premium price per kilo, because the metric that matters is cost per plate, not cost per kilo. A dearer blend with higher yield and zero batch failures routinely beats a cheaper, inconsistent one."}],["$","p","7",{"className":"rs-body","style":{"color":"#4A3728","fontSize":"1.02rem","lineHeight":1.85},"children":"If you run a multi-outlet kitchen, start with your two highest-volume gravies. Standardize the blend, fix the dosage, and measure plate cost for one month. The spreadsheet will make the rest of the argument for you."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-12 rounded-2xl p-7","style":{"background":"rgba(250,162,25,0.12)","border":"1px solid rgba(250,162,25,0.4)"},"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"rs-display","style":{"fontSize":"1.2rem","color":"#2A160C","fontWeight":600},"children":"Run the numbers on your own menu."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"rs-body mt-2","style":{"color":"#6B5040","fontSize":"0.92rem"},"children":"The cost-per-plate calculator on our products page uses the same math as this article."}],["$","$L10",null,{"href":"/products","className":"rs-btn inline-block mt-5 px-6 py-3 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#D22C2E","color":"#fff","fontSize":"0.75rem"},"children":"Open the calculator"}]]}],"$L11"]}]}]
